Across Europe, parties devoted to opposition to the EU or the abolition of the euro as a common currency are gaining influence.
Even in Germany, the Eurosceptic Alternative for Germany party - founded this year - seemed to come out of nowhere and won almost five million votes in the September federal elections, essentially &quot;sweeping&quot; the Free Democrats (the equivalent of the British Liberal Democrats) from the Bundestag.
